Description: Two corroded copper alloy objects in the shape of a flat oval grommet or ferrule, with a rectangular slot in the center. One is made of a thin leaf of metal, the other one is thicker. Probably parts of an implement (ferrule of a knife ?)
Curator's comments: The Museum register indicates a general reference to the small bronze finds mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 80 § 80, where the items are not clearly described. See also the similar item London, BM, EA 23881 (Reg. No. 1887,0208.1077).
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 80 § 80) (?)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.80, p.186, pl.28)
